==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Breeze fly
<hw>Breeze" fly`</hw>
<pr>(<?/)</pr></mhw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>brese</ets>, AS.
<ets>bri⟦oacute⟧sa</ets>; perh. akin to OHG. <ets>brimissa</ets>, G.
<ets>breme</ets>, <ets>bremse</ets>, D. <ets>brems</ets>, which are akin
to G. <ets>brummen</ets> to growl, buzz, grumble, L. <ets>fremere</ets>
to murmur; cf. G. <ets>brausen</ets>, Sw. <ets>brusa</ets>, Dan.
<ets>bruse</ets>, to roar, rush.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A fly of
various species, of the family <fam>Tabanid⟦ae⟧</fam>, noted for buzzing
about animals, and tormenting them by sucking their blood; -- called
also <altname>horsefly</altname>, and <altname>gadfly</altname>. They
are among the largest of two-winged or dipterous insects. The name is
also given to different species of botflies.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>breese</asp> and <asp>brize</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Breeze</ent>⟦br⟧
